You're home.

161
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:48,960
What's for dinner?

162
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,670
The recent days have been weary.

163
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,870
I have made fish soup for you.

164
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:54,870
I'll fill a bowl for you.

165
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:07,800
Here.

166
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:15,200
The chef made a mistake.

167
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,560
You forgot to put salt.

168
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:18,480
Really? Let me taste it.

169
00:12:35,910 --> 00:12:36,750
It was a joke.

170
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,120
It tastes great.

171
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,900
♪Then whispers of our fated meet♪

172
00:12:41,490 --> 00:12:46,000
♪Broken apart in the heat of love♪

173
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,390
What's on your mind?

174
00:12:48,390 --> 00:12:51,490
♪Lovers always misread the signs♪

175
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,390
Nothing.

